documentation.text:
@custom:function-name createVault
@param projectOwner the address of the owner and admin of the vault baing created
@param rewardToken the address of the erc20 token to reward users with
@param projectName the name of the project
@param useTokenForPayment use token for payment instead of eth
@return vault the address of the created vault
@dev this function is used to create a vault and takes a native token payment of a specified amount
which can be viewed using the creationFee function

@custom:function-name contractType
@return contractType the contract type in string
@dev this function shows the type of the contract

@custom:function-name version
@return version the contract version in semver format x.x.x
@dev this function shows the current version of the contract

@custom:function-name getVaultInfo
@param vaultAddress the vault address
@return vaultInfo the vault information stored in te factory
@dev this fuction is used to check the vault's info stored in the registry

@custom:function-name getImplementationDetails
@return implementationAddress the vault implementation the factory is currently using
@return _contractType the contract type of the implementation
@return _version the version of the implementation
@dev this function is used to check the current vault implementation details

@custom:function-name owner
@return owner the current contract owner
@dev this function is used to check who the current owner of the factory is

@custom:function-name creationFee
@return ethFee the creation fee value in ETH/Native Token
@return erc20Fee the creation fee value in ERC20 Token
@dev this function is used to check the current vault creation fee in eth

@custom:function-name feeReceiver
@return feeReceiver the address where the vault creation payments will be sent to
@dev this function is used to check the fee receiver the factory is currently using

@custom:function-name totalVaults
@return totalVaults the amount of vaults currently created by the factory
@dev this function is used to check the total amount of vaults created by the factory

@custom:function-name erc20PaymentToken
@return token token address
@dev this function allows one to view the current erc20 payment token used
in vault creation which is also an option aside from using the ETH/Native Token

@custom:function-name changeVaultFactoryOwner
@param newOwner the new contract owner
@dev this function is used to tranfer ownership and all roles from one account to another while also
removing all permissions on the previous account

@custom:function-name updateVaultInfo
@param vault the vault address that is in the factory's registry
@dev this function is used to sync the info from the vault to the factory
and can only be accessed by the owner of the vault and the factory owner/controller

@custom:function-name updateImplementation
@param newImplementation the address of the new vault implementation
@dev this function is used to update the vault implementation used in creating new vaults

@custom:function-name setFeeReceiver
@param newFeeReceiver the new fee receiver
@dev this function is used to update the fee receiver on the factory

@custom:function-name setERC20PaymentToken
@param newERC20PaymentToken the new erc20 payment token
@dev this function is used to update the erc20 payment token used to pay for the
vault creation

@custom:function-name updateCreationFee
@param newCreationFee the new creation fee that users need to pay to create a vault in ETH
@param newERC20CreationFee the new creation fee for ERC20 token payment that users need to pay to create a vault in ETH
@dev this function is used to update the vault creation fee the users needed to pay to create a new vault

@title IVault
@author Metaxona
@custom:github https://github.com/Metaxona
@custom:version 0.0.1
@dev an interface used to enforce which functions must be implemented in a vault factory contract
